{"title_page": "Everybody's Golf (2017 video game)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{about|the video game|the 1997 PS1 game|Everybody's Golf (1997 video game)|the series|Everybody's Golf}}\n{{Infobox VG\n| title = Everybody's Golf\n| image = Everybodys Golf 2017.jpg\n| developer = [[Clap Hanz]]<br />[[SIE Japan Studio]]\n| publisher = [[Sony Interactive Entertainment]]\n| caption = \n| director = \n| producer =\n| designer = \n| programmer = \n| artist = \n| writer = \n| composer = \n| series = ''[[Everybody's Golf]]''\n| platforms = [[PlayStation 4]]\n| released = {{vgrelease|NA|29 August 2017|PAL|30 August 2017|JP|31 August 2017}}\n| genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Everybody's Golf''''' is a [[Sports game|sports]] [[video game]] developed by [[Clap Hanz]] and [[SIE Japan Studio]] and published by [[Sony Interactive Entertainment]] for the [[PlayStation 4]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.playstation.com/en-gb/games/everybodys-golf-ps4/|title=Everybody\u2019s Golf|website=Playstation|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> It is the twelfth game in the [[Everybody's Golf (series)|''Everybody's Golf'']] video game series, and was released worldwide in August 2017.<ref name=RelDate>{{cite web|last=Phillips |first=Tom |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-04-20-everybodys-golf-lands-ps4-release-date |title=Everybody's Golf lands PS4 release date |publisher=[[Eurogamer]] |date=20 April 2017 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe game features character creation and customization, [[online play]] and the ability to free roam around the game's golf courses. Players are also able to drive [[golf carts]] anywhere around the course.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kimura |first=Tomoyo |url=https://blog.us.playstation.com/2015/12/07/first-details-on-new-hot-shots-golf-coming-to-ps4/ |title=First Details on New Hot Shots Golf, Coming to PS4 |publisher=[[PlayStation Blog]] |date=7 December 2015 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Development and release==\nThe game was announced at a press briefing prior to the [[Tokyo Game Show]] in September 2014, with a planned release in 2015.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\">{{cite web|last=Robinson |first=Martin |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2014-09-01-everybodys-golf-coming-to-ps4 |title=Everybody's Golf coming to PS4 |publisher=Eurogamer |date=1 September 2014 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> In the announcement, [[Shuhei Yoshida]] of Sony's [[SIE Worldwide Studios|Worldwide Studios]] said that the upcoming game would feature [[open world]] elements for the first time in the history of the series.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\"/>\n\nIn April 2017, a worldwide release date of late August was announced, along with information of pre-order offers and a [[closed beta]] test. The pre-order pack consists of a number of in-game items; a course to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the game series, a premium golf cart, exclusive character costumes and a PlayStation 4 dashboard theme.<ref name=RelDate/> The game marks the end of the alternate ''Hot Shots'' branding for the North American market, with the title ''Everybody's Golf'' being used worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/4/20/15370788/new-hot-shots-golf-ps4-release-date-everybodys-golf-sony |title=The new Hot Shots Golf is dropping the Hot Shots name |publisher=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=20 April 2017 |accessdate=21 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Hillier |first=Brenna |url=https://www.vg247.com/2017/04/21/hot-shots-take-note-everybodys-golf-has-been-announced-again/ |title=Hot shots take note, Everybody\u2019s Golf has been announced again |publisher=[[VG247]] |date=21 April 2017 |accessdate=21 April 2017}}</ref> In June 2018, an update will be released in collaboration with [[Level-5 (company)|Level-5]], who were celebrating their 20th anniversary and had a close relationship with Sony during their early years. It will add characters to the game from their ''[[Dark Cloud]]'', ''[[White Knight Chronicles]]'', ''[[Ni no Kuni II]]'', ''[[Professor Layton]]'', and ''[[Yo-kai Watch]]'' franchises.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Sato|title=Everybody\u2019s Golf\u2019s Level-5 Collaboration Has Dark Cloud, Ni no Kuni, Layton, Yo-kai Watch Costumes|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/05/22/everybodys-golfs-level-5-collaboration-dark-cloud-ni-no-kuni-layton-yo-kai-watch-costumes/|website=Siliconera|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = 78/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/everybodys-golf |title=Everybody's Golf for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=31 August 2017}}</ref>\n| Destruct = 8.5/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Devore |first=Jordan |url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-everybody-s-golf-458137.phtml |title=Review: Everybody's Golf |publisher=[[Destructoid]] |date=31 August 2017 |accessdate=31 August 2017}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 8/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Concepcion |first=Miguel |url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/everybodys-golf-review/1900-6416750/ |title=Everybody's Golf Review |publisher=[[GameSpot]] |date=5 September 2017 |accessdate=5 September 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Everybody's Golf'' received \"generally favorable\" reviews, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MC\"/>\n\n===Accolades===\nThe game was nominated for \"PlayStation Game of the Year at the [[Golden Joystick Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Gaito |first=Eri |url=https://www.bestinslot.co/golden-joystick-awards-2017-nominees/ |title=Golden Joystick Awards 2017 Nominees |publisher=Best in Slot |date=13 November 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref>  In ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Reader's Choice Best of 2017 Awards, it came in fourth place for \"Best Sports Game\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Cork |first=Jeff |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2018/01/04/reader-s-choice-best-of-2017-awards.aspx?PostPageIndex=4 |title=Reader's Choice Best Of 2017 Awards (Page 4) |publisher=[[Game Informer]] |date=4 January 2018 |accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> The game was also nominated for \"Sports Game of the Year\" at the [[D.I.C.E. Awards]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Makuch |first=Eddie |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/game-of-the-year-nominees-announced-for-dice-award/1100-6456107/ |title=Game Of The Year Nominees Announced For DICE Awards |publisher=GameSpot |date=14 January 2018 |accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> for \"Game, Franchise Sports\" at the [[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] Awards,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/ |title=Nominee List for 2017 |publisher=[[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] |date=9 February 2018 |accessdate=18 February 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180215172210/http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/ |archive-date=15 February 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/ |title=Horizon wins 7; Mario GOTY |publisher=National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers |date=13 March 2018 |accessdate=14 March 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180314070824/http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/ |archive-date=14 March 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and for \"Best Casual Game\" and \"Best Social Game\" at [[The Independent Game Developers' Association]] Awards 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last=Stephenson |first=Suzi |url=http://tiga.org/news/tiga-announces-games-industry-awards-2018-finalists |title=TIGA Announces Games Industry Awards 2018 Finalists |publisher=[[The Independent Game Developers' Association]] |date=19 September 2018 |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tiga.org/awards/2018-winners |title=2018 Winners |publisher=The Independent Game Developers' Association |date=1 November 2018 |accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External Links ==\n*{{officialwebsite|https://www.playstation.com/en-us/games/everybodys-golf-ps4/}}\n{{Everybody's Golf video games}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Golf video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4-only games]]\n[[Category:Sony Interactive Entertainment games]]\n[[Category:Everybody's Golf]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 Pro enhanced games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{about|the video game|the 1997 PS1 game|Everybody's Golf (1997 video game)|the series|Everybody's Golf}}\n{{Infobox VG\n| title = Everybody's Golf\n| image = Everybodys Golf 2017.jpg\n| developer = [[Clap Hanz]]<br />[[SIE Japan Studio]]\n| publisher = [[Sony Interactive Entertainment]]\n| caption = \n| director = \n| producer =\n| designer = \n| programmer = \n| artist = \n| writer = \n| composer = \n| series = ''[[Everybody's Golf]]''\n| platforms = [[PlayStation 4]]\n| released = {{vgrelease|NA|29 August 2017|PAL|30 August 2017|JP|31 August 2017}}\n| genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Everybody's Golf''''' is a [[Sports game|sports]] [[video game]] developed by [[Clap Hanz]] and [[SIE Japan Studio]] and published by [[Sony Interactive Entertainment]] for the [[PlayStation 4]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.playstation.com/en-gb/games/everybodys-golf-ps4/|title=Everybody\u2019s Golf|website=Playstation|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> It is the twelfth game in the [[Everybody's Golf (series)|''Everybody's Golf'']] video game series, and was released worldwide in August 2017.<ref name=RelDate>{{cite web|last=Phillips |first=Tom |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-04-20-everybodys-golf-lands-ps4-release-date |title=Everybody's Golf lands PS4 release date |publisher=[[Eurogamer]] |date=20 April 2017 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe game features character creation and customization, [[online play]] and the ability to free roam around the game's golf courses. Players are also able to drive [[golf carts]] anywhere around the course.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kimura |first=Tomoyo |url=https://blog.us.playstation.com/2015/12/07/first-details-on-new-hot-shots-golf-coming-to-ps4/ |title=First Details on New Hot Shots Golf, Coming to PS4 |publisher=[[PlayStation Blog]] |date=7 December 2015 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Development and release==\nThe game was announced at a press briefing prior to the [[Tokyo Game Show]] in September 2014, with a planned release in 2015.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\">{{cite web|last=Robinson |first=Martin |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2014-09-01-everybodys-golf-coming-to-ps4 |title=Everybody's Golf coming to PS4 |publisher=Eurogamer |date=1 September 2014 |accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> In the announcement, [[Shuhei Yoshida]] of Sony's [[SIE Worldwide Studios|Worldwide Studios]] said that the upcoming game would feature [[open world]] elements for the first time in the history of the series.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\"/>\n\nIn April 2017, a worldwide release date of late August was announced, along with information of pre-order offers and a [[closed beta]] test. The pre-order pack consists of a number of in-game items; a course to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the game series, a premium golf cart, exclusive character costumes and a PlayStation 4 dashboard theme.<ref name=RelDate/> The game marks the end of the alternate ''Hot Shots'' branding for the North American market, with the title ''Everybody's Golf'' being used worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/4/20/15370788/new-hot-shots-golf-ps4-release-date-everybodys-golf-sony |title=The new Hot Shots Golf is dropping the Hot Shots name |publisher=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=20 April 2017 |accessdate=21 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Hillier |first=Brenna 