375 |date=2005 |pmid=15944443 |doi=10.1093/molbev/msi185|display-authors=etal}} \n*{{cite journal |author=V. Battaglia|title=Y-chromosomal evidence of the cultural diffusion of agriculture in southeast Europe |pmc=2947100 |journal=European Journal of Human Genetics |volume=17 |issue=6 |pages=820\u2013830 |date=2008 |pmid=19107149 |doi=10.1038/ejhg.2008.249|display-authors=etal}}\n*{{cite journal|author=S. Cvjetan|title=Frequencies of mtDNA Haplogroups in Southeastern Europe-Croatians, Bosnians and Herzegovinians, Serbians, Macedonians and Macedonian Romani|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/8095373|journal=Collegium Antropologicum|volume=28|issue=1|date=2004|display-authors=etal}}\n*{{citation |first1=Emil |last1=Her\u0161ak |first2=Boris |last2=Nik\u0161i\u0107 |date=2007 |title=Hrvatska etnogeneza: pregled komponentnih etapa i interpretacija (s naglaskom na euroazijske/nomadske sadr\u017eaje) |trans-title=Croatian Ethnogenesis: A Review of Component Stages and Interpretations (with Emphasis on Eurasian/Nomadic Elements) |url=http://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=28729&lang=en |language=Croatian |journal=Migration and Ethnic Themes |volume=23 |issue=3}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline|Croats}}\n* {{in lang|hr}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20061109191738/http://www.matica.hr/www/mh2www.nsf/indexNovo Matica hrvatska]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061109191738/http://www.matica.hr/www/mh2www.nsf/indexNovo Review of Croatian History] at Central and Eastern European Online Library\n* {{cite web|url=http://hercegbosna.org/engleski/history.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020615173248/http://hercegbosna.org/engleski/history.html|title=Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina: History|archivedate=15 June 2002}}\n* [http://terkepek.adatbank.transindex.ro/kepek/netre/14.gif The Croatian nation at the beginning of the 20th century]\n* [http://www.croatianhistory.net/etf/art.html Famous Croats and Croatian cultural heritage]\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.matis.hr/eng/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050427225906/http://www.matis.hr/eng/|work=Croatian Heritage Foundation|title= Hrvatska matica iseljenika|archivedate=27 April 2005}}\n* [http://www.phoenixcroats.com/ Croatians in Arizona]\n\n{{Croatia topics|state=collapsed}}\n{{Ethnic groups in Croatia}}\n{{Slavic ethnic groups}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Croat people| ]]<!--please leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Croatian society]]\n[[Category:Slavic ethnic groups]]\n[[Category:South Slavs]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in the Balkans]]\n[[Category:Ethnoreligious groups in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the ethnic group known as the Croats and their descendants worldwide|information on the population of Croatia|Demographics of Croatia}}\n{{about||the medieval Catalan currency|Croat (coin)|the 17th-century mobile light military forces|Croats (military unit)}}\n{{short description|Slavic ethnic group}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n| group = Croats<br /> ''Hrvati''\n| flag = \n| flag_caption = \n| image = [[File:Pregrada folk costumes.jpg|250px]]\n| caption = Croatian [[folklorists]] in [[folk costume]]s from [[Zagorje]]\n| population = {{circa}} '''7\u20139&nbsp;million'''{{ref label|a|a}}\n| regions = {{Flag|Croatia}}<br />3,874,321 <small>(2011)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dzs.hr/Eng/censuses/census2011/results/htm/E01_01_04/e01_01_04_RH.html |title=Central Bureau of Statistics |publisher=Dzs.hr |date= |accessdate=2013-03-26}}</ref><br />{{Flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}<br />544,780 <small>(2013)</small><ref>{{cite book|title=Sarajevo, juni 2016. Cenzus of Population, Households and Dwellings in Bosnia and Herzegovina, 2013 Final Results|publisher=BHAS|url=http://www.popis2013.ba/popis2013/doc/Popis2013prvoIzdanje.pdf|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref>\n| region1 = {{Flag|United States}}\n| pop1 = 414,714 <s