 Sawa to Series Regular in Season 3 |first=Megan |last=Masters |date=July 11, 2012 |work=[[TVLine]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{Saturn Award for Best Performance by a Younger Actor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sawa, Devon}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian male actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male child actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Vancouver]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Devon Sawa\n| image        = Devon Sawa (47399571761) (cropped).jpg\n| image size   = \n| caption      = Sawa in 2019\n| birth_name   = Devon Edward Sawa\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1978|09|07}}\n| nationality  = Canadian\n| birth_place  = [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada\n| spouse       = {{marriage|Dawni Sahanovitch|2013}}\n| children     = 2\n| occupation   = Actor\n| notable_works= ''[[Little Giants]]''<br>''[[Casper (film)|Casper]]''<br>''[[Now and Then (film)|Now and Then]]''<br>''[[Wild America (film)|Wild America]]''<br>''[[Idle Hands]]''<br>''[[Final Destination (film)|Final Destination]]''<br>''[[Nikita (TV series)|Nikita]]''\n| years_active = 1992\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Devon Edward Sawa''' (born September 7, 1978) is a Canadian actor. He began acting when he was a teen, appearing in the films ''[[Little Giants]]'' (1994), ''[[Casper (film)|Casper]]'' (1995), ''[[Now and Then (film)|Now and Then]]'' (1995), ''[[Night of the Twisters (film)|Night of the Twisters]]'' (1996), ''[[Wild America (film)|Wild America]]'' (1997), ''[[Idle Hands]]'' (1999), and ''[[Final Destination (film)|Final Destination]]'' (2000).\n\nFrom 2010 to 2013, he starred as [[List of Nikita characters#Owen Elliot/Sam Matthews|Owen Elliot]] in the action spy drama series ''[[Nikita (TV series)|Nikita]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nSawa was born in [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada, the son of Joyce and Edward Sawa, a mechanic. He has two older siblings.<ref name=\"FilmReference\" /> His father is Polish, and his mother is \"a little bit of everything\".<ref name=\"feb2000int\" />\n\n==Career==\nSawa began his career in 1992 as a children's action toy spokesman. He appeared in the film ''[[Little Giants]]'', and then got his big break in ''[[Casper (film)|Casper]]'', playing the role of Casper as a human boy. In ''[[Now and Then (film)|Now and Then]]'', Sawa played Scott Wormer, the town bully, and shared a second on-screen kiss with his co-star [[Christina Ricci]] (the first was in ''Casper''). Sawa also starred in ''[[Wild America (film)|Wild America]]'', ''[[Idle Hands]]'', ''[[SLC Punk!]]'', and ''[[Final Destination (film)|Final Destination]]''. In 2000, Sawa played the title character of the [[Eminem]] music video \"[[Stan (song)|Stan]]\".<ref>D. Sawa [http://www.devonsawa.org/about-devon/filmography/stan/ ''DevonSawa.org'' Filmography: \"Stan\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001203822/http://www.devonsawa.org/about-devon/filmography/stan/ |date=2011-10-01 }}</ref> Sawa later became a voice actor by voicing [[Flash Thompson]] in ''[[Spider-Man: The New Animated Series]]''. Sawa continued steadily by appearing in several independent films including ''Extreme Dating'', ''[[Shooting Gallery (film)|Shooting Gallery]]'', ''[[Devil's Den (film)|Devil's Den]]'', ''Creature Of Darkness'', ''Endure'', ''388 Arletta Avenue'', ''[[The Philly Kid]]'', and ''[[A Resurrection (film)|A Resurrection]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Cato |first=Jason |url=http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/ae/movies/s_712792.html |title=Wilkinsburg native producing star-studded 'Sibling' in Pittsburgh |work=Pittsburghlive.com |date=2010-12-08 |accessdate=2011-07-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101216071739/http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/ae/movies/s_712792.html |archivedate=2010-12-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Creepy |first=Uncle |url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/41343/devon-sawa-meets-his-sibling |title=Devon Sawa Meets His Sibling &#124; Horror Movie, DVD, & Book Reviews, News, Interviews at Dread Central |work=Dreadcentral.com |date=2010-12-08 |accessdate=2011-07-07}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in 2010, Sawa portrayed the role of Owen Elliott on [[The CW Television Network|The CW]] action drama series ''[[Nikita (TV series)|Nikita]]''.<ref name=nikita/><ref name=nikitaowen/> In July 2012, he was promoted to series regular in season 3 of ''Nikita'', and the show ended after four seasons in 2013.<ref name=tvl120711/>\n\nIn 2017, Sawa portrayed the role of Nico Jackson in ''[[Somewhere Between (TV series)|Somewhere Between]]''; the show ended after one season. Sawa will appear as Lester Clark Jr. in ''[[Escape Plan: The Extractors]]''.{{citation needed|date=October 2018}}\n\nOn July 25, 2019, the trailer was released for ''[[The Fanatic (2019 film)|The Fanatic]]'', a thriller starring Sawa as Hunter Dunbar, an actor who is stalked by a character named Moose, played by [[John Travolta]]. The movie was directed by [[Limp Bizkit]] vocalist [[Fred Durst]].\n\n==Personal life==\nSawa is married to Dawni Sahanovitch. They have two children: a son, born in 2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2014/01/16/devon-sawa-welcomes-son-hudson/ |title=Devon Sawa Welcomes Son Hudson |date=January 16, 2014 |author=Sarah Michaud |work=People |accessdate=January 17, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140118035234/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2014/01/16/devon-sawa-welcomes-son-hudson/ |archive-date=January 18, 2019}}</ref> and a daughter, born in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/parents/devon-sawa-welcomes-daughter-scarlett-heleena/ |title=Devon Sawa Welcomes Daughter Scarlett Heleena |date=March 22, 2016 |work=People |accessdate=December 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Little Giants]]''\n|Junior Floyd\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Casper (film)|Casper]]''\n|[[Casper the Friendly Ghost|Casper McFadden]] (human form)\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Now and Then (film)|Now and Then]]''\n|Scott Wormer\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[Night of the Twisters (film)|Night of the Twisters]]''\n|Danny Hatch\n|\n|-\n|1997\n| data-sort-value=\"Boys Club, The\" | ''[[The Boys Club]]''\n|Eric\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Wild America (film)|Wild America]]''\n|Mark Stouffer\n|\n|-\n|1998\n| data-sort-value=\"Cool, Dry Place, A\" | ''[[A Cool, Dry Place]]''\n|Noah Ward\n|\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[SLC Punk!]]''\n|Sean\n|\n|-\n|1998\n|''Around the Fire''\n|Simon Harris\n|\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Idle Hands]]''\n|Anton Tobias\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Final Destination (film)|Final Destination]]''\n|[[Alex Browning]]\n|\n|-\n|2000\n| data-sort-value=\"Guilty, The\" | ''[[The Guilty (2000 film)|The Guilty]]''\n|Nathan Corrigan\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|[[E (video)|Eminem: ''E'']]\n|Stan\n|Segment: \"[[Stan (song)|Stan]]\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Slackers (film)|Slackers]]''\n|Dave Goodman\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Extreme Ops]]''\n|Will\n|\n|-\n|2005\n|''Extreme Dating''\n|Daniel Roenick\n|\n|-\n|2005\n|''[[Shooting Gallery (film)|Shooting Gallery]]''\n|Paul the Pawn\n|Direct to video\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[Devil's Den (film)|Devil's Den]]''\n|Quinn\n|\n|-\n|2009\n|''Creature of Darkness''\n|Andrew\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''Random Walk''\n|\n|Short film\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Endure]]''\n|Zeth Arnold\n|\n|-\n|2011\n| data-sort-value=\"Three Hundred Eighty-eight Arletta Avenue\" |''[[388 Arletta Avenue]]''\n|Bill Burrows\n|\n|-\n|2012\n| data-sort-value=\"Philly Kid, The\" | ''[[The Philly Kid]]''\n|Jake\n|\n|-\n|2013\n| data-sort-value=\"Resurrection, A\" | ''[[A Resurrection (film)|A Resu